[[!meta title="Calculating checksums using GtkHash"]]

You might need to calculate [[!wikipedia Checksum desc="checksums"]] to verify
the integrity of a file, for instance a file that you downloaded from the
Internet.

You can use the [<span
class="application">GtkHash</span>](http://gtkhash.sourceforge.net/)
file manager extension to calculate the checksums for a file.

Right click on a file's icon and select <span
class="guimenuitem">Properties</span> in the context menu.

In the window that pops up, activate the <span class="guilabel">Digests</span>
tab. Check the <span class="guilabel">Hash Function</span>(s) you need and
click the <span class="guilabel">Hash</span> button. Checksums will be
displayer in the <span class="guilabel">Digest</span> column.
